LAGOS  – Air Peace on Monday, December 21, 2020 operated non-stop 11 hours flight to the Island country of Jamaoica from its base at the Murtala Muhammed International Airport (MMIA), Lagos. The airline deployed one of its Boeing 777 aircraft with registration number 5N-BVE to the route. A statement by Stanley Olisa, the spokesman for the airline said that the flight departed at 17:00hrs with 132 passengers on board and had since arrived Montego Bay, Jamaica. EXPOSED - HOW LAGOS DOCTOR DISCOVERED MAJOR REASONS WHY MOST WIVES NOW HEAVILY CHEATS ON THEIR HUSBANDS AND THE PERMANENT SECRET TO SEXUALLY SATISFYING THEIR WIVES. DON'T BE A VICTIM! The statement hinted that the aircraft would once again on December 27, 2020 fly into Montego Bay for the return flight the next day. Olisa said that it was a special charter flight and was the airline’s maiden operation to the Island country, stressing that the flight further accentuated the airline’s capability to operate flights to any destination in the world. COVID-19: PenCom Postpones Retirees’ Verification, Enrolment Exercise Dangote Voted 2020 Best Company In CSR, Infrastructure Devt By PR Professionals He insisted that Air Peace had the aircraft and the requisite manpower to do so. He recalled that Air Peace had operated international flights to multiple destinations such as China, Turkey, India, Malaysia, Israel, United Kingdom, Thailand, Indonesia and recently launched scheduled direct flights to Johannesburg, South Africa, providing respite to travelers on the Lagos-Joburg-Lagos route and connecting the two giant African countries at affordable fares. SHOCKING! DOCTORS ARE MESMERIZED BY THIS NATURAL PREMATURE EJACULATION AND SMALL SIZE SOLUTION GUARANTEED TO BULLDOZE YOUR WOMAN INTO SEXUAL SUBMISSION